<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Male aedeagus with shaft strongly curvate, C-shaped, subapex dorsally with single, straight, narrow, right-angled anterodorsad, sclerotized process; gonopore apical, incised between lateral margins; shaft with lateral margins coarsely denticulate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A, B</figureCitation>
). Style apophysis straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9E</figureCitation>
). Connective elongate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9C</figureCitation>
), ratio of length to width 3.4-3.7; stem length to arm length 2.1-2.3. Pygofer process present basally on pygofer lobe, sublinear, acuminate, tubular, moderately sclerotized, orientation dorsoposteriad (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9F, G, I</figureCitation>
). Female sternite 7 with wide, shallow V-shaped notch, sternite distally narrower than base (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="male">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Male.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
n=28. Length from apex of crown to apex of tegmina 4.51-4.75 mm. Length from apex of crown to apex of abdomen 3.29-3.61 mm. Crown median length 0.34-0.36 mm. Crown length next to eye 0.28-0.30 mm. Pronotum length 0.52-0.55 mm. Head width across eyes 1.24-1.30 mm. Pronotum width 1.16-1.22 mm. Ocellus diameter 39.3-50.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; interocular distance 75.0-89.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Crown angle 120.6-124.1°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="genitalia">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Pygofer lobe.</emphasis>
Macrosetae absent, fine setae sparsely on lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9G, I</figureCitation>
). Process origin is subapically on ventral margin of pygofer lobe, sublinear, acuminate, tubular, moderately sclerotized, orientation dorsoposteriad. Pygofer lobe desclerotized, acutely angled triangle, desclerotized lobe obscure, mediad of lobe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="subgenital plate">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Subgenital plate.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Length to width 2.0-2.2 times longer than width at confluence of subgenital plate and valve. Macrosetae 9-15, variable between left and right plate. Apex of style extended half way into subgenital plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="aedeagus">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Aedeagus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Dorsal apodeme digitate, reflexed anteriad; preatrium absent; subapex dorsally with straight, right-angled, elongate, anterodorsad process (process sometimes broken, see Discussion below) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A, B</figureCitation>
). Shaft narrowly curvate, angle subtended by arc 87.1-134.3°, incised apically along dorsal and ventral margins bordering gonopore; laterally with coarse denticulation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="connective">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Connective.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Elongate, ratio length to width 3.4-3.7; stem length to arm length 2.1-2.3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="style">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Style.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apophysis straight (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9E</figureCitation>
), length of apophysis 0.3-0.4 times greatest length through sagittal plane.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="female">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Measurements.</emphasis>
n=15. Length from apex of crown to apex of tegmina 4.97-5.23 mm. Length from apex of crown to apex of abdomen 3.96-4.14 mm. Crown median length 0.38-0.41 mm. Crown length next to eye 0.31-0.33 mm. Pronotum length 0.57-0.59 mm. Head width across eyes 1.36-1.42 mm. Pronotum width 1.26-1.33 mm. Ocellus diameter 43.2-56.6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
; interocular distance 89.3-103.9 
<normalizedToken originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Crown angle 118.7-122.5°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="genital capsule">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Genital capsule.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Sternite 7.</emphasis>
V-shaped notch (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9J</figureCitation>
), relative depth of notch 0.38-0.45 times greatest length of sternite 7; ratio of length to width 0.56-0.65.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="valvifer 1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Valvifer 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Dorsal margin widely curvate, ventral margin more strongly curvate; anterior margin rounded, posterior margin acute (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. ovipositor, specimen from Nuwerus A valvula 1 B valvifer 1 C valvula 1, sculpture, subapex D valvula 1, sculpture, midsection E valvula 2 F valvula 3, apex G valvula 2, sculpture, midsection. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, E); 0.05 mm (B-D, F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493730" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. male genitalia and female ovipositor A aedeagus, lateral B aedeagus, apex, anterior C connective, dorsal D connective, lateral E style F pygofer, dorsal G pygofer, lateral H subgenital plate I pygofer lobe, lateral J sternite 7 K valvifer 1, left L valvifer 1, right." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493734" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9K, L</figureCitation>
). Ratio of length to width 1.85-2.04.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="valvula 1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Valvula 1.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Shape in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. ovipositor, specimen from Nuwerus A valvula 1 B valvifer 1 C valvula 1, sculpture, subapex D valvula 1, sculpture, midsection E valvula 2 F valvula 3, apex G valvula 2, sculpture, midsection. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, E); 0.05 mm (B-D, F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493730" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5A</figureCitation>
. Detail of sculpture, striate, at subapex (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. ovipositor, specimen from Nuwerus A valvula 1 B valvifer 1 C valvula 1, sculpture, subapex D valvula 1, sculpture, midsection E valvula 2 F valvula 3, apex G valvula 2, sculpture, midsection. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, E); 0.05 mm (B-D, F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493730" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5C</figureCitation>
), midsection (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retevolatus subspiniverpus gen. nov. &amp; sp. nov. ovipositor, specimen from Nuwerus A valvula 1 B valvifer 1 C valvula 1, sculpture, subapex D valvula 1, sculpture, midsection E valvula 2 F valvula 3, apex G valvula 2, sculpture, midsection. Scale bars: 0.5 mm (A, E); 0.05 mm (B-D, F, G)." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.54721.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/493730" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="valvifer 2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Valvifer 2.</paragraph>
